In order to study affective polarisation in France, it will be necessary to have a look at the French political and party system. This is especially important as it is not a fixed construct, and as it is one that possesses multiple specific characteristics. 

Before anything else, however, we must ask ourselves what a party system is. Persico and Haegel @haegel2017chapitre define it as "the sum of the interactions between parties in a given political system, [that] implies the coexistence of multiple parties, which find themselves engaged in relationships of a rival and cooperative nature, mainly in the electoral arena". This offers a rather comprehensive definition, which allows for a comparative perspective.
